                                Yes, if you have a valid work permit. AFTER
                                receiving your BC PNP nomination, you can
                                request a <strong
                                    >Work Permit Support Letter</strong
                                > from BC PNP. This allows you to apply for a new
                                employer-specific work permit without needing an LMIA.
